{{Infobox person | name = Haryanto Adikoesoemo | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |55|2018|03|05}}<ref name="Bloomberg profile">{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Haryanto Adikoesoemo|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=24210245&privcapId=9306270|website=Bloomberg LP|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = Indonesian | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Bradford]] | occupation = Businessman and art collector | known for = Founder, [[Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art]] | home_town = | salary = | networth = | title = President and director, [[AKR Corporindo]] | term = | predecessor = | successor = | boards = | spouse = Married | children = 5 | parents = [[Soegiarto Adikoesoemo]] | relatives = | website = }}
'''Haryanto Adikoesoemo''' (born 1962) is an Indonesian businessman and art collector.
==Early life== He is the son of Indonesian billionaire [[Soegiarto Adikoesoemo]], the founder of [[AKR Corporindo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/soegiarto-adikoesoemo/|title=Soegiarto Adikoesoemo|author=|date=|website=forbes.com|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> He earned a degree from the [[University of Bradford]] in 1983.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jenniferwang/2017/11/29/indonesias-richest-2017-heir-to-chemicals-fortune-brings-modern-art-to-indonesia/#79b9837f6873|title=Indonesia's Richest 2017: Heir To Chemicals Fortune Brings Modern Art To Indonesia|first=Jennifer|last=Wang|date=|website=forbes.com|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref><ref name="indonesiatatler.com">http://www.indonesiatatler.com/tatler-list/500list/haryanto-adikoesoemo</ref>
==Career== Adikoesoemo succeeded his father as president of AKR Corporindo in 1992.<ref name="auto"/><ref name="indonesiatatler.com"/>
He was awarded the 2008 Indonesian Entrepreneur of the Year by [[Ernst & Young]], Businessman of the Year 2012 by Forbes Indonesia magazine, and Best CEO 2012 by Corporate Governance Magazine Hong Kong.<ref name="indonesiatatler.com"/>
==Art collector== In November 2017, he opened the [[Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art]] (Museum MACAN) in [[Kebun Jeruk]], a suburb of [[Jakarta]], Indonesia, with 800 contemporary and modern art works from his collection.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/27/arts/design/jakarta-world-class-art-museum.html|title=Thanks to One Man’s Collection, Jakarta Now Has a World-Class Museum|first=Jon|last=Emont|date=27 November 2017|publisher=|accessdate=5 March 2018|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jenniferwang/2017/11/29/indonesias-richest-2017-heir-to-chemicals-fortune-brings-modern-art-to-indonesia/#39e392226873|title=Indonesia's Richest 2017: Heir To Chemicals Fortune Brings Modern Art To Indonesia|first=Jennifer|last=Wang|date=|website=forbes.com|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Adikoesoemo is married with five children.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whartonjakarta12.com/jakarta12/StaffDetails6dbd.html?Id=1332|title=The Wharton Global Alumni Forum Jakarta|author=|date=|website=www.whartonjakarta12.com|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>
