== Professional life == Grullón began working for the Banco Popular Dominicana in 1981.{{cn|date=May 2017}} He took over the position of President in 1990 when his father Alejandro Grullón was appointed Chairman of Grupo Popular's Board of Directors. In 2001 Alejandro Grullón became the parent company's chief executive.<ref name=eldia/>
